# Setup and Installation
apt install docker

# Check Docker Version
docker --version

####  Working with Docker Images  #####
1.List Docker Images
docker images

2.Pull an Image from Docker Hub
docker pull nginx
docker pull httpd

3.Remove an Image
docker rmi <image_id>

### Building Docker Images ###
Create a Dockerfile:

vi Dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine
COPY ./index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

Build an Image from a Dockerfile:
docker build -t my-nginx-image .

### Running and Managing Containers ###
1.Run a Container in Detached Mode:
docker run -d -p 8080:80 my-nginx-image

2.Check Logs of a Container:
docker logs <container_id>

3.Access a Running Container:
docker exec -it <container_id> /bin/sh

4.List Running Containers:
docker ps

5.List All Containers:
docker ps -a

6.Stop a Running Container:
docker stop <container_id>

7.Start a Stopped Container:
docker start <container_id>

8.Remove a Container:
docker rm <container_id>

9.listing only stopped containers:
docker ps -a --filter "status=exited"

10.Rename a Container
docker rename <old_name> <new_name>

11.Push an Image to Docker Hub
docker push <image_name>:<tag>

12.Pull an Image from a Private Registry
docker pull <private_registry>/<image_name>:<tag>



### Networking ###
1.List Docker Networks:
docker network ls

2.Create a Custom Network:
docker network create my-network

3.Connect a Container to a Network:
docker network connect my-network <container_id>

4.Disconnect a Container from a Network:
docker network disconnect my-network <container_id>

5.Volumes
Create a Docker Volume:
docker volume create my-volume

6.List Docker Volumes:
docker volume ls

7.Run a Container with a Volume:
docker run -d -p 8080:80 -v my-volume:/usr/share/nginx/html my-nginx-image

8.Remove a Volume
docker volume rm <volume_name>


### Cleanup ###
1.Remove All:
docker system prune -a

2.Remove All Stopped Containers:
docker container prune

3.Remove All Unused Images:
docker image prune

4.Remove All Unused Networks:
docker network prune

5.Remove All Unused Volumes:
docker volume prune
